Full 3mm wetsuit, 12lbs, too light Slight current

-KR-v7oNRmCkyiEKQ5ro.diveNotes: DM-Stephen  Pretty caves.  A few sharks in bottom, Huge fans.  Pretty little flat worm, lots of reef fish at end of dive.   Down to 110 feet no problem - 11 lbs.

-KR-v7oaEXLEBCc4fDyX.diveNotes: DM-Dexter  Incredible caves w/3 chambers. We came up inside each & looked around.  The water was fresh on the surface & made the stalactites look reflective in a mirror-like shimmer.  Out in the bay we saw mandarin fish, a giant clam.  Most of it was pretty murky & lots of trash. 12 lbs.

-KR-v7odQ86ktk52Ujdg.diveNotes: DM-Stephen  Nice tunnel.  Saw lion fish at entrance to cave. 1 yellow

-KR-v7ogAoHnfY0f4nWC.diveNotes: DM-Stephen Dove outside the channel today as current was strong inside. Best memory is purple/blue anemone cone w/3-4 clown fish in tentacles and several hundred maceral being chased by 7-8 large jacks and 4-5 shark off to the side patrolling the reef. Green

-KR-v7okO-Y84LKrHyJX.diveNotes: Hiked up & down trail to lake. Jellyfish have come back since El Nimo killed them all. Used to be 8 million, then none. Now they say between 800,000 and 1.5 million have come back. Two kinds: translucent & brown. Size of brown ones varied from 8 in diameter down to <.25.

-KR-v7or1JJUT2_ry6MM.diveNotes: DM-Stephen  Last dive! Beautiful holes.  Incredible dive.  It will be hard to find anything like this again! 12 lbs. Current @ Blue Corner 2 Yellow
